<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="460" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hitchcock</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-06-13"><hi rend="italic">June
                                        13, 1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 84.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 75 of the 25th ultimo, stating that you were advised by Count
                            Mouravieff that the Russian Government will control the construction of
                            all railways in Manchuria.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>